<subSubSection id="7364FA08A90BB77A11ADC653F62490F9" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="3971CDDDDD5E9D8249AD6F9810054EBB" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A5CBECE2B168F30EFA543A7375E285AF" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName id="16F177D66446212B8954C25E18F6B8ED" family="Rosaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. crataegifolius" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="crataegifolius">
<emphasis id="CDF932F4C4E81C1AFEA54A096E7BD38F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">R. crataegifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows on slopes, broad-leaved evergreen forests on hills, coniferous forests, thickets and roadsides. Its elevation ranges from 500-1000 m. In China, it is distributed in Anhui, Fujian, Guangxi, Jiangsu, Jiangxi and Zhejiang and overseas, in Japan.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B277E8588A188FCCD0AC96D2E747F524" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="phenology">
<paragraph id="C2D24D6C97B3FDFCAC84E9B9876D2AB5" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F9EC6FA0BF4937AF127FBADBCFE76E6F" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Flowering from May to June and fruiting from July to August.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5C67FAD281F0750919E9AA2715FFA461" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="taxonomic notes">
<paragraph id="C8AA82FA0D724272C53AA690A9A4911D" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4811F15E3F8D0D541C809F4583F16B55" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName id="24782F457EA2B5382EDB9897CACBB483" family="Rosaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. crataegifolius" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="crataegifolius">
<emphasis id="3A35C5CFCF4253E036EE472A69BEF97F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">R. crataegifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="ED9157676E8F958F2953390897B2C2A9" family="Rosaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. chingii" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="chingii">
<emphasis id="2C6759F136F9B5A9D21BB848FF776424" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">R. chingii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
H.H. Hu, the differences being: the latter leaves suborbicular, always palmately 5-parted, rarely 3- or 7-parted; flowers solitary; aggregate fruit densely hairy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
